28/05/2006
BERLIN, Germany -- Chancellor Angela Merkel told Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Friday (26 May) that her country supports Turkey's EU integration bid, but will continue watching negotiations with a critical eye. Erdogan was in Berlin attending a German-Turkish business forum. Merkel stressed that Germany expects Ankara to stick to its agreements and implement all criteria for EU membership.
In other news Friday, Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis called on Turkey to normalise bilateral ties, in order to proceed along the path to EU integration. The comment came during a speech to parliament in Athens. (Turks.US, Kathimerini - 27/05/06; TurkishPress.com, ANA - 26/05/06) 
